data.title: Health Care News
data.text:
O'Keefe family files wrongful death lawsuit against Karen Read

John O'Keefe's family filed a wrongful death lawsuit Monday against Karen Read and two bars in Canton.

DA: Driver in deadly crash during Kenny Chesney concert said he "messed up"

Michael Escolas allegedly stole a Jeep from Gillette Stadium, then crashed into a family of six that was stopped at a red light.

Severe thunderstorms in afternoon and evening forecast

The main impacts from the storms will be lightning, heavy downpours, damaging winds and the potential for hail.

How accurate are the Farmers' Almanac winter predictions?

Can the Old Farmer's Almanac or Farmers' Almanac be trusted to predict winter weather in Boston?

New information shared in 2020 murder of teen shot in bedroom

Investigators are looking for four men with Massachusetts ties in the murder of New Hampshire teen Michael Mowry.

Mass will spray for mosquitos after first human case of EEE

Massachusetts will begin spraying for mosquitos in two counties as risk for EEE - Plymouth and Worcester.

Increase in tickborne disease Alpha-Gal found on Martha's Vineyard

Alpha-Gal, which can make you allergic to meat, is spreading through the bite of the Lone Star tick on Martha's Vineyard.

Massachusetts sees first human case of EEE since 2020

A man in his 80s from Worcester County is the first person in Massachusetts diagnosed with EEE since 2020.

I-Team survey finds more than half couldn't spot a deepfake video

Could you spot a deepfake video? A WBZ-TV I-Team survey found more than half of those who took the test failed.

Inmates say they're facing retaliation after speaking out about lack of prison programs

Inmates at a prison in Massachusetts claim the Department of Correction​ retaliated against them for speaking out earlier this year about a lack of programs there.

Grandparents say DCF shares blame for 14-year-old's death in Fall River

David Almond was living with autism and doing well when the state returned him to his abusive parent. Within months, the 14-year-old was dead.

I-Team: Brigham & Women's nurses say operating room cameras violate privacy

I-Team: Report finds terrible conditions at Bridgewater State Hospital

An advocacy group wants immediate changes at a state hospital for mental patients accused of crimes in Massachusetts.

Keller: Harris loves offense. She'll need it against Trump.

Jon Keller says the rest of this campaign will be about offense and which candidate can scare voters about their opponent.

Keller: Kamala Harris presidential candidacy puts spotlight on gender and politics

Mass. GOP Senate candidates differ on Trump, borders and Warren

Jon Keller moderated a debate between Republicans looking for the party's nomination to challenge Sen. Elizabeth Warren.

Keller: Is Massachusetts really the best state to live in?

Stop & Shop to stop selling cigarettes

Boston teens practice business skills with pop-up yogurt shop

Farm in Massachusetts named a top U.S. apple picking spot

Meet the "brewstillery" making beer and spirits in Newport, Rhode Island

Newport's Castle Hill Inn provides a unique dining experience for all foodies

Visit Newport's Audrain Automobile Museum to learn more about automotive history

Boston's Prezza serving up a spicy twist on a classic cocktail

Making gourmet chocolates with Chef Delphin Gomes from M. Cacao in Amesbury

Watch Matt Damon, Casey Affleck pretend to rob a Dunkin'
